entry.def: A tier is a row or layer of something that has other layers above or below it.

example.ex: ...the auditorium with the tiers of seats around and above it.
example.tran: 四周和上方有一排排座位的礼堂

entry.def: A tier is a level in an organization or system.

example.ex: Islanders have campaigned for the abolition of one of the three tiers of municipal power on the island.
example.tran: 岛上居民发起一场运动，要求废除岛上三级市政管理层中的一级。
